@refuse_negotiations
title: Refuse to negotiate at all
choose-if: (parlament_coalition_erc_critical and player_party == "erc") or (parlament_coalition_cup_critical and player_party == "cup")
subtitle: This will be disliked by pretty much everyone, and will most probably result in new elections.
unavailable-subtitle: Sadly, we're not that critical. There are coalition options without our votes.
on-arrival: {!
    // Refusing the mandate reads as obstruction — harsher than a failed talks round.
    Q.independence_trust -= 15;
    Q.snap_blame = Q.player_party;
    Q.snap_counterparty = null; // refusal → snap_election rewards the largest rival pro-indy party
    Q.snap_severity = 0.20;
!}
call: snap_election

No one is thrilled about another election round, and the general public seems to think that governent formation was in our hands. We'll have to do some level of reconvincing before the next elections.

- @post_event: Let's hope this was for the better...

